      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        The -TION suffix is arguably the most productive word ending in English — and in Scrabble, it's your express lane to bingo plays. This 4-letter ending consumes nearly half your rack, but the payoff is enormous: with just 3 more root tiles, you're landing 7-letter words and collecting that coveted 50-point bonus. Understanding TION words transforms your mid-to-late game into a scoring machine.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">High-Scoring Words Ending in TION</h2>

      <p>These -TION words combine premium-value consonants with the suffix for maximum scoring potential. Many are playable in standard game situations and reach double-digit points without premium squares.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
